        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 9:24PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 924 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 5 miles north of Colcord to 4 miles west of
Gentry to 4 miles west of Watts. Movement was northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Gentry...                         Maysville...
Fairmount...                      Highfill...
Gravette...                       Decatur...
Siloam Springs...                 Colcord...
Springtown...                     Gallitin...
Cherokee City...                  West Siloam Springs...
Natural Falls State Park...       Bella Vista...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
northwestern Arkansas...and northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
